Principle 7: Change management
Senior management should ensure that there is an approval process that fully assesses
operational risk for all new products, activities, processes and systems.
Banks were asked to rate and describe the extent to which they have implemented the
following aspects of change management:
(a) change management risk and control assessment, and approval process (R108–R115, and
R117);
(b) roles and responsibilities (R116); and
(c) post-approval monitoring and post-implementation reviews (R120–R122).
